of spindles since play seems real tight in that area, but who knows what
might break during the tear down process. There is a wrecking yard about
thiry miles from me that said it had a front end for my 67 SC or van for
$250, but I am not sure as to its condition. But I guess that would be the
one I'm rebuilding, huh? I have recently done front breakes, wheel
cylinders, and master cylinder, (I did the late model master cylinder
upgrade with adapter plate). I really didn't want a bunch of stuff laying
around, but it sounds like the route to go, buy and rebuild another fron end
and then either sell mine or rebuild it and sell it. Hmmm, much to ponder,
lot's of explaing to the wife!
